## What

Adds an opt-in **`--all-authors`** flag (env `METRICSAI_ALL_AUTHORS`, default **off**) that makes the **security** module count PR comments from *any* author, ignoring the `github_authors` allowlist. Only the author gate is lifted — the **window** and **Conventional-Comment label** gates still apply.

## Scope: security-only

The classifier source path (`fetch_classifier_comments` and friends) carries **no** all-authors plumbing, so the `testing` module always keys off the classifier-bot author — it only counts the test-classifier's own structured `AI_CLASSIFIER_JSON` comments, where "any author" has no meaning.

## Behavior when combined with `--author`

`--all-authors` wins (the author check is bypassed). To avoid silently ignoring an explicit `--author` / `METRICSAI_GITHUB_AUTHORS`, `cli.main` logs a one-line **warning** when a non-default author list is configured alongside `--all-authors`. Covers both the flag and env-var combinations.

## Design

Chose a boolean flag over an `--author '*'` sentinel: mirrors the existing `skip_sechub` convention, avoids the shell-glob footgun of `*`, is self-documenting, and gives clean override semantics.

## Changes

- **`config.py`** — new `all_authors: bool = False` setting.
- **`sources/github.py`** — threaded `match_all_authors` through the review-scan path into `_classify`; guard becomes `if not match_all_authors and login.lower() not in authors_lower`. Classifier path untouched.
- **`cli.py`** — `--all-authors` `store_true` flag + override (mirrors `--skip-sechub`); warning when a non-default `github_authors` is set alongside it.
- **`modules/security.py`** — passes `match_all_authors=settings.all_authors`. (`testing.py` does not.)
- **Docs** — README, QUICKSTART, docs/usage, CLAUDE.md (scoped to the security module).
- **Tests** — `_classify` bypass + still-enforced window/label; CLI flow-through, default-off, and warning (fires / stays quiet); config default + env.

## Verification

- `uv run pytest` — 64 passed.
- `uv run ruff check .` / `ruff format --check .` — clean.
- `metricsai --help` shows `--all-authors`; warning verified live.

